raw_data.title: Director/Partner
raw_data.description: 10 years experience, Bachelor Degree in accounting or business, CPA License, 80 hours of continuing education and training in the past two years that meets the appropriate state CPE requirements. At least 24 of the 80 hours of CPE must meet government “Yellow Book” requirements. The director/partner is responsible for all aspects of the conduct of an engagement and for the work performed including overall project management, client relations, and final work documentation, review and reporting.

raw_data.title: Audit Manager
raw_data.description: 5 years experience, Bachelor Degree in accounting or business, CPA License, 80 hours of continuing education and training in the past two years that meets the appropriate state CPE requirements. At least 24 of the 80 hours of CPE must meet government “Yellow Book” requirements. The audit manager is responsible for directing the day-to-day accomplishment of the engagement objectives. The audit manager sets priorities, ensures daily coordination among the engagement team and monitors the progress of the engagement. The audit manager is also responsible for interaction with the client management regarding engagement issues and conflicts.

raw_data.title: Audit Senior
raw_data.description: 2 years experience, Bachelor Degree in accounting or business. CPA License or CPA candidate, 80 hours of continuing education and training in the past two years that meets the appropriate state CPE requirements is preferred. At least 24 of the 80 hours of CPE must meet government “Yellow Book” requirements. The audit senior assists the audit manager in preparing the work plan and all project deliverables and in performing critical test procedures. The audit senior also provides direct supervision to audit staff and performs the initial review of engagement working paper documentation. The audit senior is responsible for communicating issues identified during the engagement to the audit manager.

raw_data.title: Audit Staff
raw_data.description: No minimum work experience, Bachelor Degree in accounting or business. CPA License or CPA candidate, 80 hours of continuing education and training in the past two years that meets the appropriate state CPE requirements is preferred. At least 24 of the 80 hours of CPE must meet government “Yellow Book” requirements. The audit staff assists the audit senior in performing the engagement procedures and preparing and organizing engagement working papers and other engagement supporting documentation.
